I was notified yesterday morning immediately after they reopened registration and my mom got vaccinated this morning!! Thank you!

Why are the advanced navigation and notification settings only available per alert and not in the general settings? This is completely unintuitive, very easy to overlook and just frustrating to have to set endless alerts for each search rather than it be on by default. Many people will want this on by default yet it's not. You miss the first alert and then good luck if you see/hear/feel it when you want to.

Waste of money. Sometimes it "forgets" to alert me, and I'll miss dozens of changes for no reason, and yes, I did make sure it wasn't getting closed in the background. It also sometimes "forgets" my set ringtone for alerts and changes them to no ringtone forcing me to constantly check my settings. Should have stuck to the free version. I'll be looking for a better alternative that doesn't alter settings and fail to alert me

Awesome app for keeping an eye on websites for almost ANY change! I use it for tracking ALL of the following: - Application change logs from devs that don't describe changes on the store. - Prices on various shopping sites for any product I'm interested in. - Job postings on various company sites I'm interested in without cluttering up my inbox. - When a new version of my non-store apps is available. - etc.
The expansion pack isn't really needed but the app is working fine and does its goal without headaches, and that's worth supporting the dev for.

This extension is well worth the price. It works perfectly for monitoring specific changes on any webpage, even password protected pages. However, I would like pages from the same website to be able to be monitored simultaneously. It also takes about one minute for a check to be run on a password protected page, which defeats the purpose of having the checking frequency set to every second. If those two things could be improved, the app would be perfect.

The app took almost a minute to read my favorite webpage which required my login credentials. It seems that the app has to fill out my login credentials every time it checks the change in the website although I have adjusted the interval to 5 seconds. Why doesn't it save the login credentials before hand. Plus, can you use chrome engine or even the data saver feature to speedup the loading time. It's much slower than other RSS reading apps. It really makes my purchase for the expansion pack invalid.
